source.name: National Coastal Mapping Program
source.description: The U. S. Army Corps of Engineers (USACE) National Coastal Mapping Program (NCMP) is designed to provide high-resolution elevation and imagery data along U.S. shorelines on a recurring basis.  USACE Headquarters funds the NCMP to support regional sediment management, construction, operations, and regulatory functions in the coastal zone.
